{"source_key":"sha256-499e79a1c602e041fba10117966cdf45","record_index":81,"record_hash":"sha256:aeabf8ff728cdbc6eae05e7abed58603565c9cec0180aa23627e30725e5d442e","timestamp":"2026-05-11T14:17:10.063Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 5549b7\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1393\nOutput:\n     1\t# Capture Workflow\n     2\t\n     3\tThis document separates current explicit capture from future discovery. The POC\n     4\tworkflow is defined in [First POC Implementation Contract](first-poc-implementation.md).\n     5\t\n     6\t## Current Boundary\n     7\t\n     8\tThe POC supports explicit capture:\n     9\t\n    10\t```text\n    11\tbut agentlog capture \\\n    12\t  --transcript-path <path> \\\n    13\t  [--agent <codex|claude>] \\\n    14\t  [--associate-target <target>]\n    15\t```\n    16\t\n    17\tIt should not infer the current session, scan the machine, serialize GitMeta, or\n    18\tguess branch ownership. The outer `but` CLI may detect the invoking agent from\n    19\tenvironment variables, but transcript selection remains explicit.\n    20\t`--associate-target` is an explicit relationship link, not inferred ownership.\n    21\tProvider working-directory fields are not stored in transcript records.\n    22\t\n    23\tThe POC also supports hook capture:\n    24\t\n    25\t```text\n    26\tbut agentlog hook \\\n    27\t  [--agent <codex|claude>] \\\n    28\t  [--associate-target <target>]\n    29\t```\n    30\t\n    31\t`agentlog hook` reads one hook JSON object from stdin, uses the hook\n    32\t`transcript_path` and `cwd`, and exits successfully without output when\n    33\t`transcript_path` is missing. Like `capture`, it may infer the agent from the\n    34\touter `but` CLI's environment detection.\n    35\t\n    36\t## Future Inputs\n    37\t\n    38\tLater capture can accept increasingly implicit inputs, in this order of\n    39\tpreference:\n    40\t\n    41\t1. exact transcript path from a hook payload\n    42\t2. explicit provider session id\n    43\t3. agent-provided environment session id\n    44\t4. recent files in known agent directories, filtered by a later explicit\n    45\t   repository-matching strategy\n    46\t\n    47\tThe command should prefer no capture over capturing a plausible but unrelated\n    48\tsession.\n    49\t\n    50\t## Codex Discovery\n    51\t\n \n[TRUNCATED]\nectory joined with `.claude`\n    90\t\n    91\tThen look under:\n    92\t\n    93\t```text\n    94\t<claude-config-dir>/projects/<encoded-cwd>/*.jsonl\n    95\t```\n    96\t\n    97\tThe encoded project path is provider-local and lossy; use it only to narrow\n    98\tfuture discovery candidates, never as stored agentlog data.\n    99\t\n   100\t## Freshness\n   101\t\n   102\tWhen no exact transcript path is provided, freshness should consider:\n   103\t\n   104\t- file modification time\n   105\t- session metadata timestamp\n   106\t- matching session id from an environment variable or hook payload\n   107\t- a configurable maximum age\n   108\t\n   109\t## Hook Usage\n   110\t\n   111\tHook usage relies on provider payloads that include the exact transcript path.\n   112\tBoth Claude Code and Codex command hooks provide `transcript_path` and `cwd` in\n   113\tthe JSON object sent on stdin.\n   114\t\n   115\tClaude Code project settings can run the quiet hook command from `Stop`:\n   116\t\n   117\t```json\n   118\t{\n   119\t  \"hooks\": {\n   120\t    \"Stop\": [\n   121\t      {\n   122\t        \"hooks\": [\n   123\t          {\n   124\t            \"type\": \"command\",\n   125\t            \"command\": \"but agentlog hook\"\n   126\t          }\n   127\t        ]\n   128\t      }\n   129\t    ]\n   130\t  }\n   131\t}\n   132\t```\n   133\t\n   134\tCodex project config can do the same:\n   135\t\n   136\t```toml\n   137\t[features]\n   138\tcodex_hooks = true\n   139\t\n   140\t[[hooks.Stop]]\n   141\t[[hooks.Stop.hooks]]\n   142\ttype = \"command\"\n   143\tcommand = \"but agentlog hook\"\n   144\t```\n   145\t\n   146\tCodex `Stop` expects JSON on stdout when stdout is present, so the hook command\n   147\tmust stay silent on success. Claude Code also accepts silent successful command\n   148\thooks. If a future hook needs to influence the agent, add a separate command\n   149\trather than changing `agentlog hook` into an agent-control surface.\n   150\t\n   151\tReferences:\n   152\t\n   153\t- [Claude Code hooks reference](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/hooks)\n   154\t- [Codex hooks reference](https://developers.openai.com/codex/hooks)\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T14:17:10.063Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}